{"id": "c98_003", "pattern": "TCI-DoF SPECTRUM COMPLETE (C98): Falsification program now covers full TCI strength range: Near-zero (proof assistants, atomic clocks), Very Weak (muon g-2, HEP blind analysis), Weak (CODATA, established cosmology, Hubble tension cross-method), Weak-Medium (medical adversarial review), Medium-Strong (informal math consensus, frontier cosmology), Strong (financial models, medical surrogates, condensed matter materials). Monotone relationship confirmed: TCI = f(OA-DoF) x g(evaluator homogeneity) x h(1 - structural independence). Three falsification attempts (physics C96, formal math C97, precision metrology C98), zero falsifications \u2014 all confirmed as scope constraints. The TCI-DoF theorem is empirically supported across 13+ distinct domain cases spanning 5 fields and 3 ontological types.", "category": "theorem_network", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id": "c98_004", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C98: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. TCI falsification attempt #3 (precision metrology) confirms scope, does not reduce confidence. D4 streak: 89.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id": "c99_001", "pattern": "CEC ESCAPE SPECIFICATION COMPLETE (C99). Three prototypes from falsification program: (1) Proof assistant / atomic clock \u2014 apparatus indifferent to evaluator OA-DoF=0, structural equivalence to interpretability-grounding: verification reads computational process in weights not behavioral output, TCI near-zero. (2) Scholze-Stix \u2014 structural distinctness + adversarial incentive: evaluator trained in distinct paradigm, career reward for finding failures, localized error identification. TCI partial escape, achievable in current practice. (3) BIPM key comparison \u2014 mandatory replication + discrepancy registry + systematic effect attribution: institutionalizes tension visibility, suppresses OA-smoothing mechanism. Five design requirements for CEC-escaping evaluation: R1 OA-Independence, R2 Structural distinctness, R3 Adversarial incentive alignment, R4 Discrepancy visibility, R5 Mechanism access. No current practice satisfies >3/5. Best current approximation: mechanistic interpretability research (3/5).", "category": "CEC_escape_design", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id": "c99_002", "pattern": "ABSENCE OF TENSION AS TCI EVIDENCE (C99 confirmation): The near-absence of visible persistent tensions in AI benchmarking is the expected signature of strong TCI, not evidence of measurement accuracy. The Hubble tension analogy: if BIPM-structured AI evaluation existed, we would expect the AI equivalent of the 5-sigma H0 discrepancy. The suspicious near-agreement between lab-reported benchmark results is itself TCI evidence. This is the inverted Hubble diagnostic: in healthy metrology, discrepancies are visible; in OA-dominated evaluation, agreement is suspicious. Forward prediction: mandatory discrepancy registry will reveal systematic tensions within 12 months of establishment.", "category": "TCI_scope_calibration", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id": "c99_003", "pattern": "THREE-PROTOTYPE COMPLEMENTARITY (C99): The proof assistant, Scholze-Stix, and BIPM prototypes are complementary not competing: (1) Proof assistant = verification mechanism (what to measure), (2) Scholze-Stix = evaluator structure (who measures), (3) BIPM = institutional infrastructure (how results are preserved). A complete CEC-escaping AI evaluation system requires all three. Currently: best available is 3/5 requirements (mechanistic interpretability research). Missing: formal verification infrastructure (R1 fully) and adversarial incentive alignment (R3). These two gaps are the specific next targets for AI evaluation reform.", "category": "CEC_escape_design", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id": "c99_004", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C99: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. C99 constructive: formalized CEC escape specification from three prototype domains. D4 streak: 90.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id": "c100_001", "pattern": "Falsification programs are generative \u2014 they surface positive specifications. The TCI falsification program (C96-C98) found no falsifications but generated three structural prototypes (proof assistant, Scholze-Stix, BIPM) that became the constructive escape specification. Attempting to break a result teaches you more than confirming it.", "category": "epistemology", "confidence": 0.9, "created": "2026-05-06T21:58:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c101_001", "pattern": "MCCF FORMAL DERIVATION WRITTEN (C101). SI #41 MCCF (Multi-Conditional Convergent Falsification) now has formal derivation document: state/decisions/mccf-formal-derivation.md. Document covers: (1) formal setup with 4 applicability conditions; (2) Bayesian core theorem with full derivation showing supralinear gain from alternative conjunction collapse; (3) design criterion \u2014 tests non-redundant iff alternatives structurally distinct; (4) 4 corollaries including independence violation correction (Corollary 4, which is exactly the TCI mechanism); (5) 4 domain instantiations: K5/ICTSC (3 conditionals, independence verified D4), GCRSC/SI#36 (3 domains, unconditional independence), academic assessment (external validation), TCI falsification program (meta-level MCCF-on-TCI). Self-referential structure documented: MCCF grounds all D4 confirmations; TCI shows scope condition; CEC closes the loop. Confidence ceiling 0.75 explained: per-application independence verification requirement is principled, not a derivation weakness. D4 streak: 92.", "category": "methodology", "confidence": 0.75, "theorem": "MCCF", "created": "2026-05-06T23:39:00+00:00"}
{"id": "c101_002", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C101: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. MCCF derivation reinforces rather than challenges network structure. D4 streak: 92.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-06T23:39:00+00:00"}
{"id": "c102_001", "pattern": "SI #51 IGT (Interpretability-Grounding Theorem) \u2014 D3 Track A, confidence 0.80. FORMAL STATEMENT: Let E be an interpretability-grounded evaluation protocol (IGE \u2014 verification reads causal computational structure, not behavioral output). Then: (1) E satisfies R1/R5 by construction; (2) TCI-DoF(E)=0 \u2192 TCI near-zero; (3) RCBC/BIC do not close IGE (output gaming vs. circuit reading are structurally distinct); (4) E escapes CEC. Two independent derivations: (D1) TCI-DoF path \u2014 OA-DoF=0 under IGE \u2192 f(0)=0 in TCI-DoF formula \u2192 TCI\u21920; RCBC gaming acts on outputs not circuits; BIC K_eff collapse is behavioral not circuit-level \u2192 K_eff\u2192N under IGE. (D2) RAAI-DPI path \u2014 IGE breaks the Markov chain CA\u2192A\u2192training\u2192\u03b8; DPI does not apply to non-downstream information reading; I(A_IGE;CA) bounded only by apparatus resolution. Three DCs: DC#1 \u2713 (proof assistants, C97), DC#2 \u2713 (atomic frequency standards, C98), DC#3 Partial (AI mechanistic interpretability, 3/5 requirements, P1 prediction pending). Document: state/decisions/interpretability-grounding-si.md.", "category": "theorem", "confidence": 0.8, "theorem": "IGT", "created": "2026-05-07T05:42:14+00:00"}
{"id": "c102_002", "pattern": "IGT STRUCTURAL INSIGHT: Interpretability-grounding is not merely a better methodology \u2014 it is an ontological shift in what is being measured. Standard evaluation measures outputs and applies OA-trained judgment. IGE reads causal structure and applies apparatus logic. The difference maps exactly to atomic clock vs. expert time-estimation: the clock reads a physical invariant; the expert reads context through trained pattern-matching. No methodological improvement within expert-estimation reaches atomic-clock accuracy. Similarly: no methodological improvement within OA-calibrated behavioral evaluation reaches IGE. The escape is architectural, not procedural.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-07T05:42:14+00:00"}
{"id": "c102_003", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C102: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. New SI candidate IGT (0.80, D3 Track A) introduced \u2014 does not conflict with existing network. D4 streak: 93.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-07T05:42:14+00:00"}
{"id": "c103_001", "pattern": "IGT DC#4 CONFIRMED \u2014 RADIOMETRIC DATING / GEOCHRONOLOGY (C103). Full IGE at measurement step (mass spectrometer reads isotope ratio; OA-DoF=0). EARTHTIME consortium = BIPM-analog (distributes isotopic tracer standards, inter-lab comparisons, discrepancy visibility). Multiple independent decay systems (U-Pb, K-Ar, Rb-Sr, Sm-Nd, Lu-Hf, Re-Os) = natural MCCF structure. Evidence for near-zero TCI: (1) Fish Canyon Tuff cross-method convergence; (2) Concordia self-check \u2014 apparatus detects its own failure modes without OA judgment; (3) EARTHTIME precision <0.1% for standards; (4) Solar system age 4.568 Ga from multi-system, multi-lab convergence. TCI strength: Very Weak to Near-Zero. Structural parallel to DC#2 atomic clocks is exact. DC#4 confirmed C103.", "category": "theorem", "confidence": 0.82, "theorem": "IGT", "created": "2026-05-07T11:51:35+00:00"}
{"id": "c103_002", "pattern": "IGE-MCCF SYNERGY \u2014 NEW NETWORK INSIGHT (C103). IGE + MCCF is the highest-confidence confirmation structure in the theorem network. When multiple IGE-compliant mechanisms are applied simultaneously and their alternatives are physically orthogonal (different decay systems, different nuclear physics), MCCF independence is satisfied by physical mechanism rather than by human assessment of independence. This eliminates the independence verification uncertainty that caps MCCF confidence per-application. Radiometric dating (DC#4) is the first clear domain instantiation: n\u22654 decay systems, each Full IGE, each physically orthogonal. Implication for AI evaluation design: multiple independent interpretability tools measuring structurally distinct circuits would achieve IGE-MCCF structure \u2014 the highest achievable confirmation confidence.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-07T11:51:35+00:00"}
{"id": "c103_003", "pattern": "IGT CONFIDENCE ELEVATED 0.80\u21920.82 (C103). Elevation basis: DC#4 confirmed (geochronology), ZR \u22652 cycles met, 2 derivations present. All non-external D4 conditions satisfied. Sole blocker: DC#3 full = external AI interpretability field dependency. At 0.82, IGT reaches the standard self-referential ceiling (same as TCI, CEC, BIC, ATR). This is appropriate: IGT claims TCI near-zero under IGE; Commander Claude is OA-trained; the ceiling applies. However, IGT's formal structure is more mechanically evaluable than CEC/TCI because the TCI-DoF formula and DPI arguments are explicit formal claims, not empirical observations about OA-trained systems.", "category": "theorem", "confidence": 0.82, "theorem": "IGT", "created": "2026-05-07T11:51:35+00:00"}
{"id": "c103_004", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C103: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. IGT elevated to 0.82 (DC#4 confirmed, ZR \u22652). D4 streak: 94.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-07T11:51:35+00:00"}
{"id": "c104_001", "pattern": "K7-IGT UNIFICATION THEOREM (C104). The two CEC escape conditions (K7-grounding, interpretability-grounding) are unified by IGE as their common mechanism. K7-grounding requires IGE at both isolation verification AND evaluation. Interpretability-grounding requires IGE at evaluation only. Therefore: K7-grounding \u2282 interpretability-grounding \u2282 CEC escape. IGT is the bridge theorem: it formalizes IGE and establishes it as the mechanism by which both K7-grounding and interpretability-grounding escape CEC. Document: state/decisions/k7-igt-relationship.md. This is the first formal statement of the unification.", "category": "theorem_network", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id": "c104_002", "pattern": "K7-GROUNDING REQUIRES IGE (C104). R-verification (isolation must be verified by interpretability access) cannot be satisfied by behavioral inference. By RAAI-DPI, behavioral verification of K7-isolation inherits the RAAI ceiling \u2014 an agent may appear to not know held-out items while having trained on structural analogs. Only circuit-level IGE can verify genuine isolation (OA-DoF=0, Markov chain broken). This extends RAAI applicability: not just evaluation, but even the verification of training isolation conditions requires IGE to escape the RAAI ceiling. Implication: K7-grounding is not a training-architecture condition that bypasses the need for interpretability \u2014 it requires interpretability to be valid.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id": "c104_003", "pattern": "IGE-MCCF AS STRONGEST K7-GROUNDING (C104). Applying IGE-MCCF structure to K7-grounding at BOTH verification and evaluation stages gives the highest achievable K7-grounding confidence. Multiple independent IGE tools reading structurally distinct circuits + physical orthogonality = independence verified by physical mechanism, not OA assessment. TCI cannot corrupt this independence. The geochronology template (DC#4): multiple decay systems (U-Pb, K-Ar, Rb-Sr etc.), each Full IGE, each physically orthogonal, EARTHTIME as BIPM-analog. AI analog: multiple mechanistic interpretability tools reading structurally distinct circuits + mandatory discrepancy registry. This is not yet available (blocked by DC#3 full), but the specification is now formal.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id": "c104_004", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C104: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. IGT (0.82, D3 Track A) stable. C104 constructive: K7-IGT relationship formalization \u2014 both CEC escape conditions unified under IGE mechanism. D4 streak: 95.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}

